{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "615454d73e508a8fd8cf17a6", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "48", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "Material <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;has critical angle <math><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>,</mo></math> and material <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>&nbsp;has critical angle <math><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>.</mo></math> Then which of the following is true?<br />\r<br />\r(i) Light can be totally internally reflected when it passes from <math><mi>B</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&nbsp;</mi><mi>A</mi></math><br />\r<br />\r(ii) Light can be totally internally reflected when it passes from <math><mi>A</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&nbsp;</mi><mi>B</mi></math><br />\r<br />\r(iii) Critical angle for total internal reflection is <math><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub></math><br />\r<br />\r(iv) Critical angle between <math><mi>A</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&nbsp;</mi><mi>B</mi></math> is <math><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mrow></mrow><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mrow></math>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "aYqtY", "text": "(i) and (iii)", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "304O8", "text": "(i) and (iv)", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "vwMy8", "text": "(ii) and (iii)", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "CS6tL", "text": "(ii) and (iv)", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "From Snell's law<br/><br/><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03bc</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></math><br/><br/>Since, <math><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mi>\u00a0</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub></math><br/><br/><math><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>:</mo><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></math><br/><br/><math><mo>\u21d2</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03bc</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03bc</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub></math><br/><br/>When angle of incidence in the denser medium is increased even very slightly beyond the critical angle, then the ray of light is reflected back completely in the denser medium and total internal reflection takes place.  Let <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03b8</mi></math> be critical angle from medium <math><mi>A</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u00a0</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>\u00a0</mi></math>then<br/><br/><math><msub><mrow><mi>\u00a0</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03bc</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03b8</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></math><br/><br/><math><mo>\u21d2</mo><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03b8</mi></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>\u00a0</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03bc</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03bc</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03bc</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math><br/><br/><math><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi>\u00a0</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac><mo>\u00d7</mo><mfrac><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mrow></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><br/><br/><math><mo>\u21d2</mo><mi>\u00a0</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03b8</mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mrow></mrow><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mrow></math>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61964c922db938c3ec5c87e8", "6160243a86b518ff2afd9379", "6160243ae896b71d7f0f03d9", "61bb820fc1f688a120dfda9f", "61964c9102fe1de035852896", "61e7bd71a2dd607688d6c01b", "61c08989e3eba41a9e71354b", "61602437a04b762ba7dfcb47", "61602438690b07c861db4cc9", "6160243b7384a30f11cacc9e", "629109ef0299d67104ca49d5", "629f3a9295d059d5cc4d982e", "629621243e04d5d8ca7b92bd", "629f390e4eb9140dc965900d", "64eb06dd3118f713ec